The paper deals with the problem of state estimation in a linear system using measurements obtained via a 5G network architecture. This involves communication and information processing aspects, which are typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a solution based on the Gaussian Belief-Propagation (GBP) framework, which is a popular method in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Multivariate Analysis (cs.MA) sub-categories. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
